# Complete Git Commands Reference (Beginner â†’ Advanced)

This document contains **all commonly used Git commands**, organized by category. You can use this as a **study guide, interview reference, or daily DevOps handbook**.

---

## 1. Git Setup & Configuration

```bash
git --version
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@email.com"
git config --global --list
git config --list
```

---

## 2. Repository Creation & Cloning

```bash
git init
git clone <repo-url>
```

---

## 3. Status & Tracking

```bash
git status
git status -sb
```

---

## 4. Adding & Committing Changes

```bash
git add file.txt
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git commit -am "message"
```

---

## 5. Viewing History & Logs

```bash
git log
git log --oneline
git log --graph --oneline --all
git show <commit-id>
```

---

## 6. Branching

```bash
git branch
git branch -a
git branch <branch-name>
git checkout <branch-name>
git checkout -b <branch-name>
git switch <branch-name>
git branch -d <branch-name>
```

---

## 7. Merging & Rebasing

```bash
git merge <branch>
git rebase <branch>
git rebase --abort
git rebase --continue
```

---

## 8. Remote Repositories

```bash
git remote -v
git remote add origin <repo-url>
git remote remove origin
git remote set-url origin <new-url>
```

---

## 9. Push & Pull

```bash
git push
git push -u origin main
git pull
git pull origin main
```

---

## 10. Fetch

```bash
git fetch
git fetch --all
```

---

## 11. Undo & Reset

```bash
git restore <file>
git restore --staged <file>
git reset --soft HEAD~1
git reset --mixed HEAD~1
git reset --hard HEAD~1
```

---

## 12. Stash (Temporary Save)

```bash
git stash
git stash list
git stash apply
git stash pop
git stash drop
```

---

## 13. Diff & Compare

```bash
git diff
git diff --staged
git diff branch1 branch2
```

---

## 14. Tags (Releases)

```bash
git tag
git tag v1.0
git push origin v1.0
git tag -d v1.0
```

---

## 15. Cherry-pick

```bash
git cherry-pick <commit-id>
```

---

## 16. Clean & Maintenance

```bash
git clean -f
git gc
git fsck
```

---

## 17. SSH & Authentication

```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519
ssh -T git@github.com
git config --global credential.helper store
```

---

## 18. Fork & Upstream (GitHub Workflow)

```bash
git remote add upstream <original-repo>
git fetch upstream
git merge upstream/main
```

---

## 19. Useful Shortcuts

```bash
git commit --amend
git push --force-with-lease
git blame <file>
git reflog
```

---

## 20. Most Used Commands (Daily DevOps)

```bash
git status
git add .
git commit -m "msg"
git pull
git push
```

